jans that escape due\nto collisions follow the same dynamical behavior that the ones removed by\ndynamics, we would have a minor contribution of Trojans to comets and Centaurs.\nHowever, there would be some specific regions were escaped Trojans could be\nimportant such as ACOs, Encke-type comets, S-L 9-type impacts on Jupiter and\nNEOs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Nov 2018 13:11:16 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-11-02"}
